
## CLINE RULES:

color preference: glassmorphic, slightly transparent components in a modern pleasing layout. The nav bar should be about 85% transparent. 

The background should always be the darkest element, and reversed when light mode is toggled. dark mode should always be the default. It should be a deep slate-gray background, with light purplish-neon-pink gradients and blues that are already present in the template used for secondary colors, and electric blue topaz and neon turquoise for highlight elements, outlines, partitions, and borders, etc. 

Text should be professional looking but not bland or boring. 

The site should be modern and professional above flashy and gaudy or overly hyper and distracting. however it shouldnt be wikipedia page level of bland either. Finding the right balance is the goal. Use your best judgement for the best UX/UI. 



